@startuml
title Research Consent — Grant And Revoke Sequence Diagram

actor Clinician
participant "JourneyTab\n(UI)" as UI
participant "ConsentDialog /\nRevokeConsentDialog" as Dialog
participant "react-markdown" as MD
participant "client/\nresearchConsents" as Client
participant "service/\nresearchConsents" as Service
participant "patchStore" as Store

== Grant Consent ==

Clinician -> UI : Click module chip\n(amber = no consent)
UI -> Dialog : Open ConsentDialog\n(studyInfoMarkdown, moduleId,\npatientId, journeyId)
Dialog -> MD : Render studyInfoMarkdown
MD --> Dialog : Formatted study information
Dialog --> Clinician : Display info + unchecked checkbox
Clinician -> Dialog : Tick checkbox\n"I confirm the patient has been informed"
Dialog -> Dialog : Enable Confirm button
Clinician -> Dialog : Click Confirm
Dialog -> Client : grantConsent(\n  patientId,\n  researchModuleId,\n  patientJourneyId,\n  grantedByUserId\n)
Client -> Service : grantConsent(...)
Service -> Service : Check: active consent\nalready exists for\npatient + module + journey?
alt Consent already exists (idempotent)
  Service --> Client : existing Consent (unchanged)
else No active consent
  Service -> Store : patchStore:\n  append new Consent {\n    grantedAt: now(),\n    grantedByUserId,\n    revokedAt: null\n  }
  Store --> Service : updated AppState
  Service --> Client : new Consent
end
Client --> Dialog : Consent record
Dialog --> UI : Close, refetch journeys
UI -> UI : Consent chip turns green\n(active consent)

== Revoke Consent ==

Clinician -> UI : Click revoke on green chip
UI -> Dialog : Open RevokeConsentDialog\n(consentId)
Dialog --> Clinician : Show confirmation step
Clinician -> Dialog : Confirm revocation
Dialog -> Client : revokeConsent(consentId, revokedByUserId)
Client -> Service : revokeConsent(consentId, revokedByUserId)
Service -> Service : Find Consent by id\n(throws if not found)
Service -> Store : patchStore:\n  revokedAt = now()\n  revokedByUserId = userId
Store --> Service : updated AppState

note right of Store
  The original Consent record
  is never deleted — it serves
  as a permanent audit trail.
  A new grant creates a fresh record.
end note

Service --> Client : revoked Consent
Client --> Dialog : Consent record
Dialog --> UI : Close, refetch journeys
UI -> UI : Consent chip turns amber\n(no active consent)

@enduml
